reviewText: I really loved this dvd. I just recently acquired a barbell. It was loaded with 20 pounds which felt too heavy for many of the exercises, so I switched off to dumbbells (and fairly light dumbbells, too). You do not need a barbell to do this. I felt it hit all the major muscle groups, was not too long like many dvds are. Lots of balance work, and good core work at the end.

I bought this and ended up selling it.  I wanted a barbell workout but this moved way too slow for me. I think someone who is just starting with weights however may like it.  If you are intermediate or advanced, there are far better choices available.
I found this workout refreshing.  It feels as if all of the key muscles get toned and the entire workout is 30 minutes.  It is a great option for a busy schedule!

The video is a little slow and if the weights aren't heavy enough, you might not feel you achieved a good workout.  However, if you have the appropriate weights, you will really feel the burn and see results.  This is a good buy.
